    • Constructor Detail

      • MostConfidentInstances

        public MostConfidentInstances()
        Creates an instance of most confident instances. Initiates the topInstances map (key: class name; value: most confident instances for the class) by adding all existing classes in the dataset and initializing ClassifiedInstancesQueue object for each class. Each ClassifiedInstancesQueue object for the class is created with the capacity of the growthSize for that class (no. of examples from that class to be added in each iteration of co-training, growthSize in co-training.properties).

    • Method Detail

      • addInstance

        public void addInstance(ClassifiedInstance inst)
        Try to add an instance to the most confident instance list. Finds the list of classified instances to add to (dependent on the class) and tries to add an instance to that list (see ClassifiedInstancesQueue.add(ClassifiedInstance))
        Parameters:
        inst - classified instance to be added (instance id, actual label, prediction and confidence)
